{%- comment -%}
  LCP image preloads — emitted as high in <head> as possible so the browser's preload
  scanner starts fetching the largest-contentful image BEFORE the render-blocking CSS.
  (Per the Shopify speed guide: preload the LCP image, position it high in the HTML.)

  ⚠️ THE HOMEPAGE HERO IS HARD-CODED below. The layout can't read a section's
  image_picker setting, so these filenames are pinned to the current
  `image-with-overlay-banner` hero. If the homepage hero image is swapped in the theme
  editor, UPDATE the two filenames here — and confirm in the Network tab that the hero
  is fetched ONCE (the widths/media below must match the section's <picture>).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- if template == 'index' -%}
  {%- comment -%} Mobile hero (matches image-with-overlay-banner's <img>). {%- endcomment -%}
  <link
    rel="preload"
    as="image"
    href="{{ 'Homepage_hero_mobile_2.png' | file_img_url: 'master' }}"
    imagesizes="100vw"
    media="(max-width: 749px)"
    fetchpriority="high">
  {%- comment -%} Desktop hero (matches the <source media="(min-width: 750px)">). {%- endcomment -%}
  <link
    rel="preload"
    as="image"
    href="{{ 'FREESTYLE_Header_2026_Desktop_V2.jpg' | file_img_url: 'master' }}"
    imagesizes="100vw"
    media="(min-width: 750px)"
    fetchpriority="high">

{%- elsif template contains 'product' -%}
  {%- comment -%}
    PDP LCP = the SELECTED VARIANT's featured image. On load the gallery's swiper slides to
    the selected variant's slide (updateActiveVariant -> slideToSlideByDataAttribute in
    sections/main-product.liquid), so that image is what the shopper ends up looking at.

    ⚠️ URL MUST MATCH THE RENDERED <img>. The variant slide in product-gallery.liquid renders
    at a FIXED width of 581 with NO srcset:
        variant.featured_image | image_url: width: 581 | image_tag: width: 581, height: 619
    so this preload is a plain width-581 href with NO imagesrcset/imagesizes. Adding a srcset
    here would make the browser pick a different candidate than the <img> does, which
    double-downloads and triggers a "preloaded but not used" console warning.

    FALLBACK: if the selected variant has no featured image, preload the first NON-variant
    gallery slide instead (the gallery skips attached_to_variant images), matching that
    slide's responsive widths/sizes exactly — including image_tag's drop-widths-over-native.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign variant_img = product.selected_or_first_available_variant.featured_image -%}

  {%- if variant_img != blank -%}
    <link
      rel="preload"
      as="image"
      href="{{ variant_img | image_url: width: 581 }}"
      fetchpriority="high">

  {%- else -%}
    {%- assign lcp_img = blank -%}
    {%- for image in product.images -%}
      {%- unless image.attached_to_variant? -%}
        {%- assign lcp_img = image -%}
        {%- break -%}
      {%- endunless -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
    {%- if lcp_img != blank -%}
      {%- assign lcp_widths = '450, 650, 832, 1000, 1300' | split: ', ' -%}
      {%- capture lcp_srcset -%}
        {%- assign sep = '' -%}
        {%- for w in lcp_widths -%}
          {%- assign wnum = w | plus: 0 -%}
          {%- if wnum <= lcp_img.width -%}{{ sep }}{{ lcp_img | image_url: width: wnum }} {{ wnum }}w{%- assign sep = ', ' -%}{%- endif -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      {%- endcapture -%}
      <link
        rel="preload"
        as="image"
        href="{{ lcp_img | image_url: width: 832 }}"
        imagesrcset="{{ lcp_srcset | strip }}"
        imagesizes="(min-width: 1156px) 832px, (min-width: 500px) 650px, 450px"
        fetchpriority="high">
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
